# VidSlide AI Apple Style Design System - Typography Guide

## Typeface Family
Inspired by Apple's San Francisco (SF) font family

### Primary Typeface
- **SF Pro Display**
  - Usage: Headlines, titles, large text displays
  - Weights: Light (300), Regular (400), Medium (500), Semibold (600), Bold (700)
  - Characteristics: Geometric, modern, excellent readability

- **SF Pro Text**
  - Usage: Body text, UI labels, captions
  - Weights: Regular (400), Medium (500), Semibold (600)
  - Characteristics: Optimized for UI, balanced proportions

### Type Scale
Following Apple's typographic scale for consistency

```
Display Large: 48px / 1.2 line-height / SF Pro Display Bold
Display Medium: 40px / 1.25 line-height / SF Pro Display Semibold
Display Small: 32px / 1.3 line-height / SF Pro Display Medium

Headline Large: 28px / 1.35 line-height / SF Pro Display Medium
Headline Medium: 24px / 1.4 line-height / SF Pro Display Regular
Headline Small: 20px / 1.45 line-height / SF Pro Display Regular

Title Large: 18px / 1.5 line-height / SF Pro Text Semibold
Title Medium: 16px / 1.55 line-height / SF Pro Text Medium
Title Small: 14px / 1.6 line-height / SF Pro Text Regular

Body Large: 16px / 1.55 line-height / SF Pro Text Regular
Body Medium: 14px / 1.6 line-height / SF Pro Text Regular
Body Small: 12px / 1.65 line-height / SF Pro Text Regular

Caption: 11px / 1.7 line-height / SF Pro Text Medium
```

### Implementation Notes
1. Use SF Pro Display for all template titles and main content
2. Maintain consistent line-heights for vertical rhythm
3. Apply subtle letter-spacing (0.5px) for headlines
4. Use optical sizing for different screen densities
5. Ensure minimum font size of 11px for accessibility

### Fallback Fonts
- Primary: SF Pro Display, SF Pro Text
- Fallback: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif
- Web-safe: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif

### Accessibility
- All text meets WCAG 2.1 AA contrast requirements
- Minimum font size: 14px for body text, 18px for headlines
- Line height minimum: 1.5 for optimal readability
